From: suharvest <suharvest@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] v080-0004: ASR streaming single-token append-prefill guard

Phase 3b found a deterministic R2 chunk-prefill parity regression: a FINAL
prefill chunk of exactly 1 token with prior non-empty KV produced wrong sampled
last-token logits (argmax could flip; max-abs-diff ~2e+01 vs the one-shot path).
Multi-token final chunks were byte-identical (diff 0.0). KV length/commit were
correct.

Root cause (cpp/plugins/attentionPlugin/attentionPlugin.cpp deduceModeVanilla):
the AttentionPlugin distinguishes a chunked-prefill step from a vanilla decode
step PURELY by the runtime sequence length of Q:

    non-empty kvcache_start_index && qSeqLen >  1  -> kCHUNKED_PREFILL
    non-empty kvcache_start_index && qSeqLen == 1  -> kVANILLA_DECODING

So a 1-token append-prefill chunk landing on a non-empty KV cache is misrouted
to the DECODE path. In decode, RoPE position is taken from contextLength
(launchApplyRopeWriteKV(..., contextLengthTensor, ...) in
cpp/kernels/posEncoding/applyRopeWriteKV.cu computes posStartId =
kvCacheEndLens[b] - qSeqLen). The chunk path sets contextLength to the CHUNK
length (=1), so the RoPE position collapses to 0 (chunk-relative) instead of the
absolute priorKV+0, and XQA attends over sequence_lengths=1 instead of the full
KV. Hence wrong last-token logits. The chunked-prefill path instead derives the
absolute position from kvCacheEndIdxs = kvCacheStartIdx + contextLength and FMHA
attends the full KV via cuKVSeqLens. The plugin boundary has NO shape-distinct
signal: a genuine decode and a 1-token prefill-append are both qSeqLen==1 with
non-empty KV. A 1-token INTERMEDIATE chunk is equally affected (it bakes a wrong
RoPE position into the committed KV cache).

Fix: enforce the invariant in the runtime (AsrStreamingSessionRuntime) rather
than changing the plugin/engine ABI: a prefill step with qSeqLen==1 must never
run on a non-empty KV cache. We carry the trailing token of a non-final TEXT
chunk forward into the next chunk, so every step after the first (and the final
step) packs >= 2 tokens and stays on the chunked-prefill path. The first chunk
runs on an empty KV cache (kNORMAL_PREFILL, valid at length 1) and is never
deferred. Carry-over is text-only (an audio-bearing chunk binds its own per-chunk
audio embeddings and is never length 1 in practice); an audio 1-token step on a
non-empty cache is hard-refused. Carry state is committed only after the prefill
succeeds, so a refused append (capacity / guard) leaves it intact.

The one-shot path (LLMInferenceRuntime::runBaseModelPrefill ->
runBaseModelPrefillChunk(fullSpans)) is NOT touched and stays byte-identical.

The m1 spike R3 KV-continuity assertion is relaxed to accept the coalesced
intermediate boundary (kvB1 in {splitAt-1, splitAt}); the final cumulative KV
(kvB2 == totalTokens) and strict monotonicity are unchanged.

Empirical gate (orin-nx, engines-v080 Qwen3-ASR-0.6B):
  m1 N-1 (1-tok final) splits 30/29, 40/39, 64/63, 100/99:
    argmax MATCH, max-abs logit diff = 0.000000e+00 (was ~1.9-2.3e+01 FAIL).
  m1 multi-token splits 64/32, 40/17, 100/50, 64/62, 40/38: still diff 0.0.
  m2 session lifecycle: PASS x3.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
--- a/cpp/runtime/asrStreamingSessionRuntime.h
+++ b/cpp/runtime/asrStreamingSessionRuntime.h
@@ -159,6 +159,15 @@
     DecodingInferenceContext mContext; //!< Session-scoped inference context.
     rt::Tensor mChunkAudioEmbedding;   //!< Reusable FP16 buffer for per-chunk encoded audio.
 
+    //! @brief Carried trailing token of a previous non-final TEXT chunk (v080-0004).
+    //! @details Single-token append-prefill guard: the AttentionPlugin routes a qSeqLen==1
+    //!          prefill step on a non-empty KV cache to the DECODE path (wrong RoPE position /
+    //!          attention length), so we never emit a 1-token prefill step after the first chunk.
+    //!          The trailing token of a non-final text chunk is held here and prepended to the
+    //!          next chunk, guaranteeing every subsequent (and the final) step packs >= 2 tokens.
+    //!          Empty in steady state. Never holds an audio-bound token.
+    std::vector<int32_t> mPendingTextTail;
+
     bool appendChunkImpl(std::vector<int32_t> const& chunkTokenIds, rt::audioUtils::AudioData const* mel,
         bool isFinalChunk, cudaStream_t stream);
 };
--- a/cpp/runtime/asrStreamingSessionRuntime.cpp
+++ b/cpp/runtime/asrStreamingSessionRuntime.cpp
@@ -123,15 +123,106 @@
         return false;
     }
 
-    // Overflow guard: this chunk must not push the cumulative positions past the MRope/KV capacity
-    // the session was initialized for (spec R3 invariant).
-    if (mMaxPositions > 0 && mAppendedTokens + static_cast<int32_t>(chunkTokenIds.size()) > mMaxPositions)
+    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+    // Single-token append-prefill guard (v080-0004).
+    //
+    // The AttentionPlugin distinguishes a chunked-prefill step from a vanilla
+    // decode step PURELY by the runtime sequence length of Q:
+    //   deduceModeVanilla() (cpp/plugins/attentionPlugin/attentionPlugin.cpp):
+    //     non-empty kvcache_start_index && qSeqLen > 1  -> kCHUNKED_PREFILL
+    //     non-empty kvcache_start_index && qSeqLen == 1  -> kVANILLA_DECODING
+    // So an append-prefill chunk of EXACTLY 1 token landing on a NON-EMPTY KV
+    // cache is misrouted to the decode path. In decode, RoPE position is taken
+    // from contextLength (launchApplyRopeWriteKV(..., contextLengthTensor, ...) →
+    // posStartId = contextLength - qSeqLen). The chunk path sets contextLength to
+    // the CHUNK length (=1), so the position collapses to 0 (chunk-relative)
+    // instead of the absolute priorKV+0, and XQA attends over sequence_lengths=1
+    // instead of the full KV. The sampled logits are wrong (argmax can flip).
+    // Multi-token chunks (qSeqLen>1) route correctly and are byte-identical.
+    // This corrupts BOTH a 1-token FINAL chunk (wrong sampled token) and a
+    // 1-token INTERMEDIATE chunk (wrong RoPE position baked into the KV cache).
+    //
+    // There is no signal at the plugin boundary to disambiguate a 1-token
+    // prefill-append from a genuine decode by shape alone, so we enforce the
+    // invariant in the runtime instead: a prefill step with qSeqLen==1 must
+    // never run on a non-empty KV cache. We coalesce by carrying the trailing
+    // token of a non-final TEXT chunk forward into the next chunk, so every
+    // subsequent (and the final) prefill step packs >= 2 tokens. The FIRST chunk
+    // runs on an empty KV cache (priorKV==0 ⇒ kNORMAL_PREFILL, which is valid at
+    // length 1), so it is never deferred. Carry-over is applied only to
+    // text-only chunks: an audio-bearing chunk binds its own per-chunk audio
+    // embeddings, and an audio chunk is never length 1 in practice, so its
+    // token↔embedding correspondence is left untouched.
+    //
+    // A non-empty KV cache is equivalent to "at least one chunk already
+    // committed" (beginAsrSession resets KV and commits nothing), i.e.
+    // mChunkCount > 0.
+    bool const priorKvNonEmpty = (mChunkCount > 0) || !mPendingTextTail.empty();
+
+    // Build the effective token slice for this step: any carried text tail from a
+    // previous non-final text chunk, followed by this chunk's tokens. NOTE: member
+    // state (mPendingTextTail) is NOT mutated until the prefill below succeeds, so a
+    // refused append (capacity / 1-token guard) leaves the carry state intact.
+    std::vector<int32_t> effectiveTokens;
+    bool const textOnly = (mel == nullptr);
+    if (!mPendingTextTail.empty())
     {
-        LOG_ERROR("appendChunk: chunk would exceed session capacity (appended=%d + chunk=%zu > maxPositions=%d)",
-            mAppendedTokens, chunkTokenIds.size(), mMaxPositions);
+        // A pending tail can only have come from a previous TEXT chunk. It is safe
+        // to prepend to a text chunk (pure text gather) and to an audio chunk
+        // (the deferred text token takes a text embedding; the audio chunk's audio
+        // embeddings are indexed by its own audio-pad positions and are unaffected).
+        effectiveTokens.reserve(mPendingTextTail.size() + chunkTokenIds.size());
+        effectiveTokens.insert(effectiveTokens.end(), mPendingTextTail.begin(), mPendingTextTail.end());
+        effectiveTokens.insert(effectiveTokens.end(), chunkTokenIds.begin(), chunkTokenIds.end());
+    }
+    else
+    {
+        effectiveTokens = chunkTokenIds;
+    }
+
+    // Decide whether to defer this step's trailing token. We defer when the step
+    // is NOT final, is text-only, and running the remainder now would still leave
+    // a valid prefill (effectiveTokens.size() >= 2 so the deferred-1 step has >=1
+    // token). The carried token guarantees the NEXT step (final or not) packs
+    // >= 2 tokens, keeping it on the chunked-prefill path even if the producer
+    // hands us a single trailing token.
+    bool const deferTail = (!isFinalChunk && textOnly && effectiveTokens.size() >= 2);
+
+    std::vector<int32_t> stepTokens;
+    std::vector<int32_t> nextPendingTail; // committed to mPendingTextTail only on success.
+    if (deferTail)
+    {
+        nextPendingTail.assign(effectiveTokens.end() - 1, effectiveTokens.end());
+        stepTokens.assign(effectiveTokens.begin(), effectiveTokens.end() - 1);
+    }
+    else
+    {
+        stepTokens = std::move(effectiveTokens);
+    }
+
+    // Hard invariant: a 1-token prefill step must never run on a non-empty KV
+    // cache (would be misrouted to the decode path). After the carry-over logic
+    // above this can only happen for an audio-bearing chunk of length 1 on a
+    // non-empty cache, which is not produced by any real ASR chunker. Refuse
+    // rather than emit silently-wrong logits.
+    if (stepTokens.size() == 1 && priorKvNonEmpty)
+    {
+        LOG_ERROR("appendChunk: refusing a 1-token prefill step on a non-empty KV cache (chunk %d, audio=%d) — "
+                  "this would be misrouted to the decode path and produce wrong logits",
+            mChunkCount, static_cast<int32_t>(!textOnly));
         return false;
     }
 
+    // Overflow guard: this step must not push the cumulative positions past the MRope/KV capacity
+    // the session was initialized for (spec R3 invariant). Use the actual committed step length
+    // (carry-over preserves the cumulative token count across deferral).
+    if (mMaxPositions > 0 && mAppendedTokens + static_cast<int32_t>(stepTokens.size()) > mMaxPositions)
+    {
+        LOG_ERROR("appendChunk: chunk would exceed session capacity (appended=%d + step=%zu > maxPositions=%d)",
+            mAppendedTokens, stepTokens.size(), mMaxPositions);
+        return false;
+    }
+
     // Encode the mel chunk (if any) into a per-chunk audio embedding buffer and bind it for THIS
     // chunk's embedding lookup. Text-only chunks pass no audio embeddings.
     rt::OptionalInputTensor audioEmbeds = std::nullopt;
@@ -145,17 +236,19 @@
         audioEmbeds = std::optional<std::reference_wrapper<rt::Tensor const>>(std::cref(mChunkAudioEmbedding));
     }
 
-    // Append-only prefill: pack ONLY this chunk's slice onto the committed KV cache. Sampling is
+    // Append-only prefill: pack ONLY this step's slice onto the committed KV cache. Sampling is
     // enabled only on the final chunk.
     std::vector<rt::SpanI32> chunkSpans;
-    chunkSpans.emplace_back(chunkTokenIds.data(), chunkTokenIds.size());
+    chunkSpans.emplace_back(stepTokens.data(), stepTokens.size());
     if (!mRuntime.appendPrefillChunk(mContext, chunkSpans, audioEmbeds, /*sampleAfterPrefill=*/isFinalChunk))
     {
         LOG_ERROR("appendChunk: prefill chunk %d failed", mChunkCount);
         return false;
     }
 
-    mAppendedTokens += static_cast<int32_t>(chunkTokenIds.size());
+    // Commit carry state only now that the prefill has succeeded.
+    mPendingTextTail = std::move(nextPendingTail);
+    mAppendedTokens += static_cast<int32_t>(stepTokens.size());
     ++mChunkCount;
     if (isFinalChunk)
     {
@@ -176,6 +269,7 @@
     mMaxPositions = 0;
     mAppendedTokens = 0;
     mChunkCount = 0;
+    mPendingTextTail.clear();
     mStatus = AsrSessionStatus::kIdle;
 }
 
